According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Flash Storage market was valued at USD 62.4 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 68.9 billion in 2025 to USD 132.7 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 9.8% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth as enterprises increasingly adopt high-speed, low-latency storage solutions to support AI workloads, cloud computing, big data analytics, and 5G infrastructure. Continuous advancements in NAND flash technologies, including 3D NAND and Quad-Level Cell (QLC) architectures, are enhancing storage density while reducing costs, making flash storage more accessible across enterprise and consumer applications. The rapid replacement of traditional hard disk drives (HDDs) with solid-state drives (SSDs) is further accelerating market expansion.
